    <description>Extract Dataverse metadata and generate Power BI TMDL/PBIP semantic models with automatic table relationships, calendar tables, and incremental change detection.</description>
    <summary>XrmToolBox plugin for generating Power BI semantic models from Dataverse metadata</summary>
    <releaseNotes>
v1.2026.5.21 — Comprehensive update with storage modes, preservation logic, and redesigned change preview.

New Features:
- Storage Mode Support — DirectQuery, Dual (All/Select), and Import mode per semantic model with per-table overrides
- Export/Import Configurations — Share model configs as JSON files between machines or team members
- Change Preview Redesign — Grouped TreeView with impact analysis (Safe/Additive/Moderate/Destructive), filter toggles, and detail pane
- Incremental Update Preservation — LineageTags, user relationships, column descriptions, formatting, annotations, and platform IDs preserved across rebuilds
- Table Rename Detection — Detects renamed tables via source comment and carries over all customizations
- Vista Folder Picker — Modern Explorer-style folder dialogs with breadcrumbs, search, and favorites

Improvements:
- FetchXML View Filtering — 20+ operator support including relative dates, user context, string matching, and logical grouping
- Date Relationship Dedup — Stale date relationships automatically cleaned up when date field changes
- Connection Type Warnings — Change preview warns when switching between TDS and FabricLink
- Attribute List Performance — Pre-sorted cache for instant table/filter switching
- Comprehensive README — New sections for Storage Modes, Configuration Management, Change Preview, and FetchXML operators

Bug Fixes:
- Fixed false "Storage Mode Change" warning when using Dual Select mode (Dual vs DualSelect equivalence)
- Fixed false "query structure changed" warning for Boolean fields in FabricLink (GlobalOptionsetMetadata vs OptionsetMetadata)
- Fixed DATEDIFF in older-than-x FetchXML operators, date table relationship display names, Font GDI resource leaks
    </releaseNotes>
